ANKARA , December 1 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- Iraq 's Kurdistan Democratic Party -LRB- KDP -RRB- killed seven rebels of the outlawed Kurdish Workers ' Party -LRB- PKK -RRB- coming from Iran , the semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported today .
The agency said that KDP forces surrounded a group of about 200 PKK militants Saturday , who infiltrated from Iran and are trying to shelter themselves between Pirbela and Snath camps in northern Iraq .
The KDP exchanged heavy fires with the PKK guerrillas near Snath camp in the region at Sunday noon and shot dead seven PKK rebels in the clash , said the agency .
It added that it is difficult for the PKK rebels to enter into Turkey due to the strict security measures taken by the Turkish government troops so that some PKK militants have tried to shelter themselves in northern Iraq .
